<subSubSection pageNumber="679" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="679">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="679">Note:</emphasis>
On the assumption that this name was first published in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="679">Kongl. Svenska Vetensk. Acad. Handl.</emphasis>
16: 176, t. 6, f. 1. 1755), Le Duc (in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="679">Sida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
16: 628. 1995) designated as type the figure published there. However, this article by Linnaeus (for the period 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jul–Aug–Sep">Jul-Aug-Sep</normalizedToken>
) appears to be pre-dated by an account of the species in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="679">
<volumeTitle>
<volumeTitle>Centuria I Plantarum</volumeTitle>
</volumeTitle>
</emphasis>
(Feb 1755), from which this figure is absent, and cannot therefore be original material for the name.
</paragraph>
